==English==
====Etymology====
From Bantu; compare [[jumby]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈzɒmbi/}}
'''Hyphenation''': zom&middot;bie

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[snake]] [[god]] in [[religions]] of [[West Africa]] and elsewhere
# {{cattag|fiction}} A person that is [[undead]]; a reanimated corpse.
# A person that is [[apathetic]].
# An information worker who has signed a non-disclosure clause, in return for employment.
# {{computing}} A [[process]] or [[task]] which has [[terminated]] but was not removed from the list of processes, typically because it has child processes that have not yet terminated.
# {{computing}} A [[PC]] [[affect]]ed by [[malware]] which causes it to send out large amounts of [[spam]] or perform [[DDOS]] attacks without the user’s knowledge.
# A [[drink]] of [[rum]] and [[fruit]] [[juice]]s

